title: Delaunay Triangulation for Haiti Collapsed Buildings 7/13/10
name: Delaunay Triangulation for Haiti Collapsed Buildings 7/13/10
description:
Created a Delaunay triangulation surface in QGIS to get an idea of what the spatial pattern was for the seismic activity in relation to the collapse of buildings.  Original data came from OSM and was derived from the analysis of GeoEye imagery.

Original data from: http://finder.geocommons.com/overlays/20381
